                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12876510" author="codahale" created="Tue, 8 Jun 2010 01:14:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adds the JVM detection logic from Debian&apos;s tomcat6 package to the Debian init.d script.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12877654" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 11 Jun 2010 00:20:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We probably don&apos;t want to include jdk 1.5 directories on the search path, since we require 1.6&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12877661" author="codahale" created="Fri, 11 Jun 2010 00:30:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch, which chooses between the Sun JRE and the OpenJDK JRE, preferring Sun.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12877671" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 11 Jun 2010 00:47:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(tested and it works for me against openjdk still, but i&apos;m a little puzzled as to why since it chops off the jre/ part of the old path)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12877809" author="hudson" created="Fri, 11 Jun 2010 12:45:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #462 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/462/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/462/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    allow using sun jdk w/ debian init script.  patch by Coda Hale; reviewed by jbellis for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1174&quot; title=&quot;Debian packaging should auto-detect the JVM, not require OpenJDK&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1174&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1174&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
